   <pb facs="9"/>
   <head>Thomas Dranta</head>
   <l>BElla viros{que} canit Sadlerus tempora belli,</l>
   <l>Castra acies fossas, spicula, tela, duces.</l>
   <l>Perbellè facit is, bellum qui rite repandit:</l>
   <l>Aurea per bellum pax solet essere dux.</l>
   <l>Edocuit bellum, bellum Deus ipse probauit:</l>
   <l>Si bellum, belli tunc probatilli librum.</l>
   <l>Sic Sadlere tibi multum pax bella{que} debent:</l>
   <l>Sic Deus &amp; librum, te probat at{que} tuum.</l>
